s:59:"Give your joints a break with these 7 chair yoga exercises.";i:3;s:138:"Osteoarthritis OA a joint disease that causes painful swelling most often in the knees hips and hands affects 30 million people in the US.";i:4;s:120:"Research has shown that one of the most effective ways to reduce pain and improve quality of life for people with joint.";i:5;s:208:"Chair Yoga is a gentle adapted form of yoga which can accommodate your individual level of flexibility and support you in building core body strength improved range of motion and an overall reduction in pain.";i:6;s:171:"Find a qualified Chair Yoga teacher in your area to support you in building a Chair Yoga practice that is adapted to your health and any chronic pain or injury conditions.";i:7;s:128:"Chair yoga provides many options for those recovering from surgery with unstable balance or needing a cane walker or wheelchair.";i:8;s:52:"Remember movement that is pain-free is good for you.";i:9;s:91:"If you are experiencing shoulder pain standing poses with hands on hips are a great option.";i:10;s:125:"If you are experiencing knee pain using a chair and stretching and flowing through your spine and arms will help the rest of.";i:11;s:117:"As the name suggests Chair Yoga takes place in a chair so theres no getting up and down from a yoga mat on the floor.";i:12;s:175:"It is a gentle style of an ancient practice that incorporates many of the mind-body benefits of traditional yoga including stress relief and improved strength and flexibility.";i:13;s:39:"Chair Yoga Relieves OA Pain Study Says.";i:14;s:55:"Chair Yoga For Seniors And Those With Limited Mobility.";i:15;s:28:"12 Poses To Try Pain Doctor.";i:16;s:44:"A Restorative Yoga Routine for Chronic Pain.";i:17;s:114:"Restorative yoga turns on the healing relaxation response by combining gentle yoga poses with conscious breathing.";i:18;s:101:"Below you will learn four restorative yoga poses that may be practiced on their own or in a sequence.";i:19;s:65:"There are several factors that make restorative yoga so relaxing.";i:20;s:148:"Chair yoga is an ideal exercise for those suffering from conditions such as chronic pain carpal tunnel syndrome osteoporosis and multiple sclerosis.";i:21;s:122:"It may also benefit people over a certain age who have trouble moving through the up and down motions of traditional yoga.";i:22;s:42:"Chair yoga allows them to stay stabilized.";i:23;s:141:"Hosted by yoga instructor Amanda Hamp When we use yoga for managing chronic pain stress the goal is to quiet the nervous system and the mind.";i:24;s:125:"So using a chair is not just a practice for those with injuries or mobility issues although it is perfect for these students.";i:25;s:69:"Its a route to more quiet and subtle movements in order to shift our.";i:26;s:107:"Regular at-home yoga is a great tool to help with the daily functions of those suffering from chronic pain.";i:27;s:79:"Join me for this 25 min practice that you can do on a mat or seated in a chair.";i:28;s:146:"This gentle yoga practice helps you to explore these tools of yoga and how they can support you on your journey toward healing and feeling better.";i:29;s:117:"Chair Yoga Leg Sequence Lift your right thigh a few inches and then straighten your knee extending your heel forward.";i:30;s:24:"Then drop your leg back.";i:31;s:29:"Do the same on your left leg.";i:32;s:35:"Repeat four more times on each leg.";i:33;s:44:"On the last lift keep your thigh lifted and.";i:34;s:63:"Yoga has been shown to help with various kinds of chronic pain.";i:35;s:128:"So it makes sense that people with RA might look to the practice as a potential tool to deal with flares and everyday aches and.";i:36;s:171:"If you live with chronic pain yoga can help reduce physical symptoms like pain stiffness and swelling while the meditative aspect of yoga can improve depression and sleep.";i:37;s:15:"Use a chair or.";i:38;s:189:"A recent randomized pilot study tracked two groups of low-income older adults 